OL,3,CMSPs to back Holyrood Budget that
OL,4,CShona Robison says will 'make lives
OL,5,Cbetter'
OL,7,FMSPs will approve the Scottish
OL,8,FGovernment's Budget for the coming
OL,9,Fyear ` with Finance Secretary Shona
OL,10,FRobison insisting her tax and spending
OL,11,Fplans will "make lives better for
OL,12,Fpeople in Scotland".
OL,14,FShe spoke out ahead of the final vote
OL,15,Fon Holyrood's Budget on Wednesday
OL,16,Fevening, saying the proposals would
OL,17,Fhelp improve the NHS and also assist
OL,18,Fthose struggling with the cost of
OL,19,Fliving.
OL,26,@sD@LOUtD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1771981383
OL,3,CMSPs to back Holyrood Budget that
OL,4,CShona Robison says will 'make lives
OL,5,Cbetter'
OL,7,FBut a deal with the Scottish Liberal
OL,8,FDemocrats, together with Labour having
OL,9,Falready made clear its MSPs will
OL,10,Fabstain in the vote, means the
OL,11,Fminority SNP government can be certain
OL,12,Fof getting its 2026-27 Budget package
OL,13,Fthrough the Parliament.
OL,15,FHowever Scottish Conservative finance
OL,16,Fspokesperson Craig Hoy said that MSPs
OL,17,F"must belatedly come to their senses
OL,18,Fand vote down the SNP's reckless and
OL,19,Funfair Budget".
OL,26,@yD@AOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1771981383
OL,3,CMSPs to back Holyrood Budget that
OL,4,CShona Robison says will 'make lives
OL,5,Cbetter'
OL,7,FHe raised concerns about the
OL,8,F"ballooning benefits bill", saying
OL,9,Fthat SNP ministers are in "complete
OL,10,Fdenial" about this and expect "hard-
OL,11,Fworking Scots to continually pick up
OL,12,Fthe tab for it".
OL,14,FWarning that "Scotland faces a welfare
OL,15,Ftimebomb", the Tory said: "Benefits
OL,16,Fspending must be reined in so that
OL,17,Fbills can finally be cut for scunnered
OL,18,FScots taxpayers."
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@ZO]qD@[OUrD@GO]rD@_OUtD@OO]vD@
OL,26,ANOUwD@IO]wD@[OUzD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
